HR-Analytics

Explore the dynamics of human resources through insightful Analytics in my HR Analytics project. This project is about HR metrics, providing valuable insights to optimize workforce management and enhance organizational performance.
## Processes
This project’s primary goal is to create Dashboard, but before dashboard it is necessary to clean and organised the data, To understand,clean and organised the data I use R programming on R Studio Platform. After, ensure the data is cleaned and organised, I push the data into ta database, then I use Apache Superset to create interactive Dashboard. Though There is not much opensource Hosting site to Embedded Superset dashboard, so I put all those screenshot in this R Markdown.

# delete the newly created column due to miss mapping
data <- data %>% select(- Attrition_vector)
# create again that new variable
data <- data %>%
  mutate(Attrition_vector = ifelse(Attrition == "Yes", 1, 0))
# see the mapping 
data %>% select(Attrition,Attrition_vector) %>% head(10)

knitr::opts_chunk$set(echo = TRUE)
# connecting with database
con <- dbConnect(odbc::odbc(),
                 driver = "PostgreSQL Unicode",
                 server = "localhost",
                 port = 5432,  
                 database = "codeone",
                 uid = "postgres",
                 pwd = "13599")
